From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrey Smirnov <andrey.smirnov@siderolabs.com>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 13:30:00 +0000
Subject: slab: backport k{,v}{m,z}alloc_flex helpers

Linux 6.18.x backports kmalloc_obj/kzalloc_obj/kvmalloc_obj and their
_objs array variants from the upstream type-safe allocator series, but
omits the matching _flex helpers for variable-length-array-tail
structures.

Out-of-tree modules (notably DRBD 9.3.2's drbd_sender.c, which calls
kzalloc_flex(*fb, values, fifo_size, GFP_NOIO)) assume that whenever
kmalloc_obj is available, kzalloc_flex is too -- drbd's compat layer
gates the kzalloc_flex Coccinelle transform on COMPAT_HAVE_KMALLOC_OBJ.
With the incomplete backport this leaves kzalloc_flex undeclared and
the module fails to build.

Add the _flex aliases as thin wrappers around struct_size() so the
existing kmalloc_obj cocci assumption holds. This matches the upstream
intent (the comments above already reference kmalloc_(obj|objs|flex)).

Signed-off-by: Andrey Smirnov <andrey.smirnov@siderolabs.com>
---
 include/linux/slab.h | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

--- a/include/linux/slab.h
+++ b/include/linux/slab.h
@@ -1011,18 +1011,29 @@
 #define kzalloc_objs(P, COUNT, GFP)			\
 	__alloc_objs(kzalloc, GFP, typeof(P), COUNT)
 
+#define kmalloc_flex(P, FAM, COUNT, GFP)		\
+	kmalloc(struct_size(&(P), FAM, COUNT), GFP)
+#define kzalloc_flex(P, FAM, COUNT, GFP)		\
+	kzalloc(struct_size(&(P), FAM, COUNT), GFP)
+
 /* All kvmalloc aliases for kmalloc_(obj|objs|flex). */
 #define kvmalloc_obj(P, GFP)				\
 	__alloc_objs(kvmalloc, GFP, typeof(P), 1)
 #define kvmalloc_objs(P, COUNT, GFP)			\
 	__alloc_objs(kvmalloc, GFP, typeof(P), COUNT)
 
+#define kvmalloc_flex(P, FAM, COUNT, GFP)		\
+	kvmalloc(struct_size(&(P), FAM, COUNT), GFP)
+
 /* All kvzalloc aliases for kmalloc_(obj|objs|flex). */
 #define kvzalloc_obj(P, GFP)				\
 	__alloc_objs(kvzalloc, GFP, typeof(P), 1)
 #define kvzalloc_objs(P, COUNT, GFP)			\
 	__alloc_objs(kvzalloc, GFP, typeof(P), COUNT)
 
+#define kvzalloc_flex(P, FAM, COUNT, GFP)		\
+	kvzalloc(struct_size(&(P), FAM, COUNT), GFP)
+
 #define kmem_buckets_alloc(_b, _size, _flags)	\
 	alloc_hooks(__kmalloc_node_noprof(PASS_BUCKET_PARAMS(_size, _b), _flags, NUMA_NO_NODE))
 
